"title": "5729: one flesh",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5729",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A sign and expression of the inseparable union between husband and wife. This is not only physical but emotional, mental and spiritual. It is also used to describe the union between Jesus Christ and the church.</p>\n<h2>One flesh describes the inseparable union between husband and wife</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:22-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:22–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:16\">1CO 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:28-Eph5:29\">EPH 5:28–5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31\">EPH 5:31</a></p>\n<h2>One flesh refers to sexual union which Scripture describes in various ways</h2>\n<h3>To lie with</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:1\">GEN 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:17\">GEN 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:25\">GEN 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:31-Gen19:35\">GEN 19:31–19:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:21\">GEN 29:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:23\">GEN 29:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:30\">GEN 29:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:19\">1SA 1:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:11\">2SA 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:24\">2SA 12:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:21\">2SA 16:21</a></p>\n<h3>To come together</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18\">MAT 1:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>To have union or unite with</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:15-1Cor6:16\">1CO 6:15–6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:25\">MAT 1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:5\">MAT 19:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7\">MRK 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31\">EPH 5:31</a></p>\n<h3>Natural relations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a></p>\n<h2>One flesh expresses an intimacy encouraged by God</h2>\n<h3>Only within heterosexual marriage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:4–19:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10\">LEV 20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:28\">MAT 5:27–5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:11\">1CO 5:9–5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9\">1CO 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:4\">1CO 7:4</a></p>\n<h3>Intimate relations between members of the same sex are unnatural and wrong</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:22\">LEV 18:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9\">1CO 6:9</a></p>\n<h2>One flesh describes the union between Jesus Christ and the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:31–5:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:16-1Cor6:17\">1CO 6:16–6:17</a></p>",
